      <hedline>
        <hl1>Heavy Metal</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert Camp letter on Frank Cammuso and Hart Seely's August 27 Bookend essay notes warning label on new profssional cookstove (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Aug. 27 Bookend, Frank Cammuso and Hart Seely's ''Important: Read This First,'' was hands down the best ever. Recently my wife and I bought a professional cookstove from G.E. It took four brawny men to drag it into position. This stove will never move again. On the door handle of the oven was a bright orange sign saying warning -- do not tip over.</p>
        <p>Robert Camp  Exeter, N.H.</p>
      </block>
